<span id="freeTextContainer7853347917493594284">Another fast-paced and thrilling read from Kimberly Belle!<br/><br/>I really enjoyed The Marriage Lie (2016) and her latest did not disappoint. I was quickly wrapped up in Beth&apos;s escape plan from her overbearing and abusive husband. She is on the run, but you won&apos;t imagine the obstacles that she will have to face. She knows that he will be hot on her trail, BUT can he catch her?<br/><br/>Cat and mouse? or Mouse and cat?<br/><br/>If you&apos;re looking for a fast summer read with a clever plot, some different POV&apos;s and scattered r</span>
  <span id="freeText7853347917493594284" style="display:none">Another fast-paced and thrilling read from Kimberly Belle!<br /><br />I really enjoyed The Marriage Lie (2016) and her latest did not disappoint. I was quickly wrapped up in Beth's escape plan from her overbearing and abusive husband. She is on the run, but you won't imagine the obstacles that she will have to face. She knows that he will be hot on her trail, BUT can he catch her?<br /><br />Cat and mouse? or Mouse and cat?<br /><br />If you're looking for a fast summer read with a clever plot, some different POV's and scattered red-herrings to keep the tension ramped up and compelling, this one is highly entertaining.<br /><br />Thanks to EW for my review copy. Book is out on June 25,2019</span>
